<HEADLINE>
<P>
CONGRESS VOTES NO ON PAY RAISE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
I am more and more convinced our government could best be improved, not by pay 
increases, but with only one elected term of six to eight years, with one-third 
or one-fourth of the legislative body replaced every two years. A retiring 
representative could choose to run for a Senate seat, or vice versa, accept a 
government appointment or otherwise serve, but never run for reelection to the 
same office. 
</P>
<P>
We don't need lifetime politicians! We need people who want to serve our 
country without concern of "special interest groups" to be reelected. Rather 
than 94% of incumbents returning (who really has a chance), new faces with new 
ideas could invigorate our governing bodies. Perhaps "crisis" government would 
finally end. I would also carry this one-term policy to state, city and county 
governments. 
</P>
<P>
RITA SIEMONS 
</P>
<P>
Redondo Beach 
</P>
</TEXT>
