<HEADLINE>
<P>
CONGRESS VOTES NO ON PAY RAISE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
I was glad to see Congress vote against its pay raise. It restored my faith in 
the "by the people, for the people" theory of government. Congress does listen. 
</P>
<P>
I do believe, however, that our servants in government are underpaid. 
</P>
<P>
The solution? A 50% raise in pay by raising your hand and saying aye? Well, 
that seems a little unrealistic. But why not that same percentage spread over 
four or five years? 12.5% a year is much easier to swallow, for me anyway. 
</P>
<P>
It seems time is the real reason. Some members wouldn't see the full amount of 
increase. But what better way to show the voters their true motivations in 
seeking public office? 
</P>
<P>
Maybe that is the real problem. 
</P>
<P>
ERIC C. NORDLING 
</P>
<P>
Cardiff by the Sea 
</P>
</TEXT>
