<P>
VALLEY ROUNDUP: INVESTOR BUYS ADDITIONAL SHARES IN HCC INDUSTRIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
An investor raised his stake in HCC Industries, an Encino maker of airtight 
electronic connectors, from 9.2% to 10.1% of HCC's stock. 
</P>
<P>
In a filing with the Securities and Exchange Commission, Walter Neubauer said 
he bought 15,700 additional HCC common shares, raising his overall ownership to 
167,700 shares. 
</P>
<P>
The latest shares were bought between Jan. 19 and 26 at prices ranging from 
$4.38 to $6.13 a share, the filing said. 
</P>
