<HEADLINE>
<P>
VALLEY ROUNDUP: FORTUNE, FAIRBANKS &amp; HAAS REACH GAS WELL AGREEMENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Fortune Petroleum Corp. of Agoura Hills has reached agreement with Fairbanks 
&amp; Haas, a Ventura energy concern, on a joint venture to drill for gas in 
northern Kern County. 
</P>
<P>
Under the agreement, Fortune will drill the initial well by March 31 on a 
1,800-acre site that Fortune leases. The cost of drilling, expected to total 
about $180,000, will be paid by Fairbanks &amp; Haas. 
</P>
<P>
If the initial drilling results in a producing gas well, Fortune and Fairbanks 
&amp; Haas would become partners in operating the well, Fortune Chairman Cecil 
Basenberg said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
