<HEADLINE>
<P>
VALLEY EARNINGS: TEKELEC REPORTS PROFITS TRIPLE IN 4TH QUARTER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Tekelec said its fourth-quarter profit nearly tripled from a year earlier, when 
the Calabasas company's earnings were hurt by its decision to drop two product 
lines. 
</P>
<P>
Tekelec, which makes testing equipment for the telecommunications industry, 
said its net income for the quarter that ended Dec. 31 rose to $1.47 million, 
or 36 cents a share, from $500,000, or 13 cents a share, a year earlier. Sales 
soared to $9.34 million from $5 million. 
</P>
<P>
When Tekelec discontinued the two product lines a year ago, it took a $381,000 
after-tax charge that depressed its earnings. 
</P>
<P>
For all of 1988, Tekelec's profit jumped to $5.35 million, or $1.31 a share, 
from $749,000, or 20 cents a share, in 1987. Annual sales nearly doubled to 
$32.8 million from $17 million. 
</P>
</TEXT>
