<HEADLINE>
<P>
SLUMS BENEFIT CHARITIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
For the last two years, City Atty. James K. Hahn has asked that sentences for 
Los Angeles landlords convicted of maintaining slum conditions include 
requirements that they make contributions to organizations assisting the 
homeless and underprivileged. In all, slumlords have given more than $150,000 
to such organizations, with the leading beneficiary being Las Familias del 
Pueblo, a Skid Row social service agency. 
</P>
