into the league. They wanted to raise the possibility that Barry may not get 
in." 
</P>
<P>
NFL spokesman Joe Browne confirmed that William Sanders met last Wednesday with 
Jay Moyer, the league's executive vice president. 
</P>
<P>
"It was strictly an informational meeting about our eligibility rules," Browne 
said. 
</P>
<P>
Should Sanders, a running back, go to the NFL next fall, he would be the first 
routine college junior to make such a jump. Sanders has until April 10 to apply 
in writing for eligibility for the draft later that month. 
