P.M. BRIEFING; 
</P>
<P>
USX, KOBE STEEL PLAN JOINT VENTURE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
PITTSBURGH 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
USX Corp. said today it plans to establish a joint venture with Kobe Steel Ltd. 
of Japan to operate the U.S. company's specialty bar and tubular products plant 
at Lorain, Ohio. 
</P>
<P>
Each partner will own 50% of the joint venture, which will buy the Lorain plant 
and become the new employer of the approximately 3,000 workers who operate the 
plant. 
</P>
<P>
USX withheld the proposed purchase price in a printed statement. 
</P>
<P>
The deal will be the first investment in the U.S. steel industry for Kobe, 
Japan's leading producer of steel bar products. A Kobe official in Tokyo said 
the partnership will help the company adjust to steel product requirements of 
Japanese vehicle makers in the United States. 
</P>
</TEXT>
