<TEXT>
<P>
The Indiana Pacers are attempting to trade for veteran NBA guard Randy Wittman, 
an Indianapolis native and former player at Indiana University, general manager 
Donnie Walsh confirms. The 6-foot, 6-inch Wittman, a three-year starter with 
the Atlanta Hawks, has played sparingly this season with the Sacramento Kings, 
averaging 4.0 points in 29 games. 
</P>
