CRASH TOTALS EARNHARDT'S RACE CAR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times staff and wire service reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
DAYTONA BEACH, Fla. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Dale Earnhardt escaped injury today in a crash that destroyed his Grand 
National race car during practice at Daytona International Speedway. Earnhardt, 
a three-time Winston Cup champion who campaigns his own Grand National car, was 
running a hot lap at the end of the session when he tangled with a car driven 
by L. D. Ottinger. Neither driver was injured, but Earnhardt's Chevrolet was 
too badly damaged to repair. Ottinger's crew was working frantically on his 
Pontiac in an effort to repair it in time to qualify for Saturday's Goody's 300 
Busch Grand National stock car race. Earnhardt, who had been planning to run in 
both the Goody's race and Sunday's Daytona 500, will concentrate on the Winston 
Cup event. 
</P>
