IN BRIEF; 
</P>
<P>
SEELY TO COACH COLT SPECIAL TEAMS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times staff and wire service reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
INDIANAPOLIS 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Brad Seely, offensive line coach the past five years at Oklahoma State, signed 
today as special teams coach with the Indianapolis Colts. Seely, who previously 
served as offensive line coach under the Colts' Ron Meyer at Southern Methodist 
University, was the fifth former assistant to Meyer hired since the end of the 
1988 season. 
</P>
<P>
The other four are offensive coordinator Larry Kennan, offensive line coach 
Dante Scarnecchia, receivers coach Milt Jackson and defensive line coach Bill 
Muir. At Oklahoma State, Seely managed the blocking schemes that helped Barry 
Sanders set 23 NCAA rushing records en route to the 1988 Heisman Trophy. 
</P>
